gomodel:SYNGO_863  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper examines the localization of kappa-type opioid receptor in dopaminergic terminals at the nucleus Accumbens using electron microscopic immunocytochemistry.\nFig. 4 shows a DAT-containing terminal in contact with kappa-type immunoreactive dendritic spines. The dendritic spine shows kappa-type opioid receptor labeling at the postsynaptic density and along extrasynaptic portions of the plasma membrane. The fraction of kappa-type opioid receptor immunoreactivities which opposes DAT labeling is quantified in table 1.\n\n2/7/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: 'Rats were anesthetized with 100 mg/kg i.p. sodium pentobarbital and perfused through the ascending aorta with 1) 10 ml of heparin (1,000 U/ml) in saline; 2) 50 ml of 3.75% acrolein (Polysciences, Warrington, PA)'" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_863" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

